quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  23,75,"And if We have mercy on them and remove whatever distress they have, they would still persist obstinately in their rebellion, wandering blindly."
  23,76,"And We have already seized them with punishment, but they did not turn humble to their Lord, nor do they supplicate in humility,"
  23,77,"] until when We will open against them the door of a severe punishment, they will be taken aback in despair."
  23,78,"And He is the One who created for you the ears and the eyes and the hearts. Little you are grateful."
  23,79,"And He is the One who created you on the earth and it is He unto whom you will be gathered together."
  23,80,"And He is the One who gives life and brings death and it is He to whom belongs the alternation of night and day. So, do you not understand?"
  23,81,"80] But they said like what the earlier people had said."
  23,82,"They said, "Is it that, when we will die and become dust and bones--is it that we will be raised again?"
  23,83,"This is what we and our fathers had been promised with before. It is nothing but the tales of the ancients.""
  23,84,"] Say, "Whose is the earth and all those therein if you have knowledge?""
  23,85,"They will say, "Allah's." Would you still pay no heed?"
  23,86,"Say, "Who is the Lord of the seven heavens and the Lord of the Great Throne?""
  23,87,"They will say, " (All this belongs) to Allah". Say, "Would you still not fear Allah?""
  23,88,"Say, "Who is the One in whose hand lies the kingdom of everything and who gives protection and no protection can be given against him, if you have knowledge?""
  23,89,"] They will say, " (All this belongs) to Allah." Say, "Then from where are you being bewitched?""